---
// About section
---

<section id="about" class="mb-16 md:mb-20">
  <h2 class="text-sm font-mono text-[var(--color-accent)] mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider">
    About
  </h2>
  
  <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[0.75fr_1.25fr]">
    <p class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight">
      Mechanic brain, product instincts, full-stack hands.
    </p>
    <div class="space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        I started as an Australian Army vehicle mechanic, which is a useful origin story for software: stay calm, trace the system, find the thing that is actually broken, and leave it easier to fix next time.
      </p>
      
      <p>
        These days I build web apps, internal tools, Salesforce integrations, agent runtimes, and the boring infrastructure that keeps ambitious ideas from falling over.
      </p>
      
      <p>
        <span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] font-medium">I do not need every project to share one aesthetic.</span> 
        A control plane, a communication coach, an email engine, and client delivery work all have different audiences. The domain should make that clearer, not flatten it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="section-divider"></div>
